\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
restart the Quince micro:
 unplug USB,
 reconnect USB
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Now the Quince micro is ready to function as a WCH-LinkE apter.
 After connecting it to another CH32 target (for example another Quince micro),
 the second microcontroller can be programmed with,
 for example:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
\begin_inset listings
inline false
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

wlink flash blink.bin
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The connection to a second Quince micro is done by connecting the pins SWDIO and SWCLK of both boards.
\end_layout

